title: How Climate Choices Shape Future Rainfall Across U.S. Regions?
description: Visualized 165 years of U.S. rainfall data alongside future climate projections to show how precipitation patterns are changing over time. The historical record (1850–2014) reveals a steady upward trend with natural variability, which I use as the baseline before transitioning into model-based projections (2015–2100).
